[the night before]
- peel and soak in cold water to remove starch

[boil & ruffle - ≅ 2hr ahead of time]
- chop into large pieces to account for lost ruffled edges
- boil in strongly seasoned water (seawater) for 35 mins, stirring every 5 mins for ruffled edges
- strain water (optionally keep for making gravy)
- season again and leave to steam for 5 mins
- cover and shake for even further ruffled adges

[oily roast - 1 hr ahead of time]
- heat veg oil and optionally duck fat for flave to 180°C
- pour half oil into deep roasting tray
- place tatos into oil and pour remaining over top
- into 180°C overn for 40 mins
- add garlic & rosemary (aromats)
- back in for 10 more mins


SHORTER ALTERNATE VERSION
- peel potatos, cut into roughly 50mm-sided pieces, soak for a few hours
- boil for 25 mins instead of 35 mins
- bring oil pan to 200°C initially
- bake for 30 mins
- add aromats
- bake for 10 mins
- remove oil, add rack, baste one last time
- bake for 10 mins
